ere are a million theories about why QWERTY was invented \u2014 the most common one holds that its creator wanted to make sure old typewriter mechanisms didn\u2019t crash into each other as you whacked the keys \u2014 but almost everyone agrees, it\u2019s not the best way", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24118418/keyboard-layout-qwerty-microsoft-copilot-surface-netflix-thumbs", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "A better keyboard than QWERTY", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-02T13:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Brother HLL2370DW-XL laser printer\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/-guaDv7E3uWSO9eNaGvirrLbAAY=/0x0:564x376/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73248918/Brother_HLL2370DW_XL_laser_printer.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo: Brother</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"fMB20f\">It\u2019s been over a year since I last <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23642073/best-printer-2023-brother-laser-wi-fi-its-fine\">told you to just buy a Brother laser printer</a>, and that article has fallen down the list of Google search results because I haven\u2019t spent my time loading it up with fake updates every so often to gain the attention of the Google search robot.</p>\n<p id=\"ozQlEY\">It\u2019s weird because the <em>correct answer</em> to the query \u201cwhat is the best printer\u201d has not changed, but an <a href=\"https://www.cnet.com/tech/computing/best-printer/\">entire</a> <a href=\"https://www.forbes.com/sites/forbes-personal-shopper/article/best-home-printer/\">ecosystem</", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/2/24117976/best-printer-2024-home-use-office-use-labels-school-homework", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Best printer 2024, best printer for home use, office use, printing labels, printer for school, homework printer you are a printer we are all printers", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-02T13:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A promotional image for the Artifact app.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/NVz3cm-3cvIIrpvGQy_dLc9fAIY=/0x0:2880x1920/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73248923/unnamed.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The Artifact app will be gone soon \u2014 but the Yahoo News app might start to be more like it.</em> | Image: Artifact</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"tfKWDg\">Instagram\u2019s co-founders built a powerful and useful tool for recommending news to readers \u2014 but could never quite get it to scale. Yahoo has hundreds of millions of readers \u2014 but could use a dose of tech-forward cool to separate it from all the internet\u2019s other news aggregators. And so, the two sides are joining forces: Yahoo is acquiring Artifact, the companies announced on Tuesday.</p>\n<p id=\"UG0sxP\">The two sides declined to share the cost of the acquisition, but both made clear Yahoo is acquiring Artifact\u2019s tech rather than its team. Mike Krieger and Kevin Systrom, Artifact\u2019s c", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/2/24118436/yahoo-news-artifact-acquisition", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Yahoo is buying Artifact, the AI news app from the Instagram co-founders", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-02T12:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Illustration of Xbox\u2019s chatbot.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/s4tCHO1prpx93cncW4JRepB1-NI=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73248811/247070_Xbox_AI_chatbot__CVirginiaA.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>A mockup of what Microsoft\u2019s Xbox chatbot looks like.</em> | Cath Virginia / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"IRFM2E\">Microsoft is currently testing a new AI-powered Xbox chatbot that can be used to automate support tasks. Sources familiar with Microsoft\u2019s plans tell <em>The Verge </em>that the software giant has been testing an \u201cembodied AI character\u201d that animates when responding to Xbox support queries. I understand this Xbox AI chatbot is part of a larger effort inside Microsoft to apply AI to its Xbox platform and services.</p>\n<p id=\"pCcsSN\">The Xbox AI chatbot is connected to Microsoft\u2019s support documents for the Xbox network and ecosystem, and can respond to questions and even process game refunds fr", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/2/24118728/microsoft-xbox-ai-chatbot-testing", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Microsoft is working on an Xbox AI chatbot", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-02T11:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Illustration of the iMessage behind a gavel.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/K8ZzyKGYpJL3OAS9yOaQG_Hqce8=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73248739/STK468_APPLE_ANTITRUST__CVIRGINIA_N.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Cath Virginia / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"Cgtj3D\">Of all the allegations that the <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/3/21/24105363/apple-doj-monopoly-lawsuit\">Department of Justice</a> has laid at Apple\u2019s door, the most contentious is perhaps its salvo over security and privacy. Apple has warned that if the DOJ gets its way, Apple products \u2014 especially the iPhone \u2014 will be less secure for users. Meanwhile, the DOJ claims that Apple\u2019s much-touted <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2021/4/27/22405474/apple-app-tracking-transparency-ios-14-5-privacy-update-facebook-data\">privacy features</a> are pretextual.</p>\n<p id=\"4RTFEE\">The complaint in the DOJ\u2019s antitrust lawsuit against Apple ", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/2/24107719/iphone-security-apple-doj-monopoly-antitrust-lawsuit", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Will the Apple antitrust case affect your phone\u2019s security?", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-02T10:48:43+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Twitch logo\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Oi6lk02TnWZbx7x9CI7jUGleyRM=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73248728/STK044_VRG_Illo_N_Barclay_4_twitch.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The record was broken during a 15-hour stream on April 1st.</em> | Illustration by Nick Barclay / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"83wLsH\">Game developer Jason Thor Hall, better known by the moniker Pirate Software, has set a new Twitch Hype Train world record, with his channel reaching <a href=\"https://twitter.com/PirateSoftware/status/1774922709967003924\">level 106 on April 1st</a>. Once the Hype Train was initiated, it took Hall roughly three hours to beat his previous <a href=\"https://twitter.com/PirateSoftware/status/1735036339022913567\">level 55 world record from December</a>, with viewers contributing 54,380 gifted subs (alongside regular subscriptions) and 8,225,386 Bits \u2014 likely earning Hall <a href=\"https://dotesports", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/2/24118755/twitch-hype-train-world-record-piratesoftware-bits-gifted-subs", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Twitch\u2019s Hype Train record smashed again by Pirate Software", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-02T10:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Meta logo in white on red background\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/MLMYx9A53FALUQPObGz0imMRQso=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73248668/STK043_VRG_Illo_N_Barclay_5_Meta.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration: Nick Barclay / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"IoFzRt\">\u201cThe ability to know somebody\u2019s age and try to protect privacy at the same time can be challenging,\u201d says Meta\u2019s Global Head of Safety Antigone Davis. Meta has been <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/15/23962153/meta-online-age-verification-app-stores\">advocating for app store operators </a>like Apple and Google to be in charge of verifying users\u2019 ages and soliciting parental consent for app downloads. Now, it\u2019s using its own virtual reality Quest store as a model for how it thinks that should work.</p>\n<p id=\"mxQFof\">Meta is prompting Quest 2 and 3 users to reenter their birthdays so that it can place accounts in the appropriate age", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/2/24118204/meta-age-verification-quest-store-antigone-davis", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "How Meta\u2019s global head of safety approaches online age verification", "user": null, "vote": 0}]